  "title": "Should hide pagination whenever having 1 page or no results",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nMaybe a Bug\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\nThere are 2 contexts:\r\n- Having only one page: should not display pagination, it has no meaning.\r\n- Don't have any results: when users click on a link which in the past it has some results, but currently it doesn't; or navigate to a menu with 0 items.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\nShould not display page nagivation.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What browsers are impacted? Which versions?**\r\nChrome latest.\r\n\r\n**What project are you opening an issue for?**\r\n- react-instantsearch\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\n2.2.4\r\n\r\n",
